{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-01545/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-01545"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:15:45"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["extreme close-up"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["overhead"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, zoom"]}},{"label":{"none":["Lighting"]},"value":{"none":["high key"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["single shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A pair of hands hold a slip of paper that reads: \"For the hungry boy! my name is Alma\""]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01545/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-01545","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01545/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-01545"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01545/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01545/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01545/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01545/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01545/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01545/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01545/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01545/canvas/1/689e4167-13fb-4fed-8ac1-1474ad6c1e97","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T20:35:50.176Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>The name Alma means “soul” or “nourishment,” an appropriate choice given the role she'll play in Reynolds’s life. She will provide the nourishment he desires: one that is equal parts maternal, loving, and cruel. She’ll also serve as his soul in the sense that she transforms his life completely and brings energy to an otherwise placid, predictable existence. PTA swears that the fact that she shares her name with Alfred Hitchcock’s wife, Alma Reville, is entirely accidental (Bell, “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW221191013 BCX0\" href=\"https://www.bfi.org.uk/sight-and-sound/features/paul-thomas-anderson-phantom-thread-1950s-london-haute-couture-gothic-romance-daniel-day-lewis-vicky-krieps\"><u>Paul Thomas Anderson on Phantom Thread</u></a>”).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01545/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:819.339416058394,509.28832116788317,266.85766423357677,137.64963503649642"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01545/canvas/1/1bfb68e1-9f84-4a42-a7db-ab29cd6ebd77","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T20:36:02.631Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Reynolds is, indeed, a “hungry boy.” His outsized breakfast also symbolizes his voracious (if repressed) appetites for love, sex, maternal attention, and domestication. Alma clearly recognizes this desire in the man whom she has just met.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01545/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:977.5839416058393,125.24452554744528,160.46715328467167,159.31751824817525"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01545/canvas/1/05ca3e8a-8000-4367-b246-93ea072c39a9","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T20:36:16.646Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>Reynolds’s breakfast exudes sexual overtones. From the plump and phallic sausages to the fleshy bacon, it embodies his “hunger” (that is, desire) and gives visual representation to the tension between the two characters from their first moments together.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01545/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:1244.2335766423357,195.5912408759125,141.4817518248176,606.6897810218977"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01545/canvas/1/90981492-4a6f-4be9-b0ea-d51f127be141","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T20:36:34.564Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>As Alma pours the water for tea, she raises the kettle to produce a long stream. There’s an element of power here, as if she’s showing Reynolds the control she can wield. This moment is <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW59089299 BCX0\" href=\"https://digbmc.github.io/pt-annotated/items/phan-15620.html\"><u>echoed</u></a> near the end of the film during the dramatic (and sensual) second poisoning. In general, tea and tea kettles symbolize power and status throughout the film.&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01545/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:13.083941605839371,49.27007299270073,161.9671532846716,113.56204379562044"}}},{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01545/canvas/1/5b7114fb-9a2e-4624-9d6d-dfc7d0b55ff4","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T20:36:46.846Z","creator":"Clara Smith","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>PTA himself has a taste for large breakfasts, something Daniel Day-Lewis would tease him for during the production of <em>There Will Be Blood</em> when he would see PTA “ordering five times the normal amount” (Bell, “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW191457892 BCX0\" href=\"https://www.bfi.org.uk/sight-and-sound/features/paul-thomas-anderson-phantom-thread-1950s-london-haute-couture-gothic-romance-daniel-day-lewis-vicky-krieps\"><u>Paul Thomas Anderson on Phantom Thread</u></a>”). When asked about his perfect breakfast, he responded: “I personally prefer my eggs over-easy; toast kinda crispy; loads and loads of butter – I’m the opposite of Reynolds, I mean I really just fucking lather it up – chives on top; not too much salt; avocado; black coffee. I don’t eat meat but in the old days I’d probably throw some bacon and sausage in there. I could go on and on about breakfast” (Woodward, “<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW191457892 BCX0\" href=\"https://lwlies.com/interviews/paul-thomas-anderson-phantom-thread\"><u>Paul Thomas Anderson</u></a>”).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-01545/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:17.518248175182514,181.64233576642334,160.3467153284671,106.75182481751824"}}}]}]}]}